caption: A little bit of old world Italy in the Bronx.  We shared a little salad and a plate of seafood pasta.  The salad had lightly grilled pear and goat cheese.  The salad was seasoned and lightly dressed.  The seafood pasta a perfectly cooked.  They were very generous with the seafood; there were three large scallops, 5-6 very large shrimp, 5-6 juicy little clams and 6-7 mussels.  This place takes social distancing seriously.  Loads of air flow. They take information for contact tracing too.  Hopefully this restaurant survives the pandemic.  We want to come back.

March 30, 4:30 PM. By 4:20 PM peopke began lining up at the entrance waiting for the doors to open. By 4:30 the amount of people waiting was quite substantial. At 4:30 the 2 hostesses arrive. By the time they got organized, by the time everyone entered and by the time we were seated it was time to watch the 5:00 news on the TV overlooking the bar. The rush to practically service everyone at the same time manifested itself in the quality of the service. Three times water was spilled while refilling our glasses. One time on my daughter's cell phone. In the rush to separate our pizza slices a mushroom found itself flying from the table but, luckily, landing safely on my wife's lap. The ham and mushrooms on the pizza were in short supply. When found the ham was absolutely tasteless and when a mushroom was located it had the slightest hint that it was indeed a mushroom. The crust was soggy. The fish platter, relatively speaking, was an upgrade from the pizza, but fishy in name only. When a waiter mentions tap water or sparkling water in the same breath, one assumes both are free. Otherwise the menu offers the sparkling water and its corresponding price. We were quite annoyed that Zero Otto Nove, in a sneaky way, charged us $8 for the bubbles. CHEAP. UNPROFESSIONAL. TASTELESS.

We ordered a nice Pinot Grigio (Banfi 2016) to go with our meal.  My son had Pizza Diavolo and thoroughly enjoyed it.  Prices are moderate to high.   We went on a Sunday (30 minute wait) and the restaurant was full so the kitchen was a bit backed up.  Our orders took a little longer to be served.  Service however, was impeccable - bussers constantly refilling water glasses, dropped fork replaced immediately, etc.  We will try this restaurant again - maybe on a weekday evening instead.
